ISRC
    9 bytes total


    4 bytes
        6 bits x 5 = 30 bits

        2 bits unused

        NABBLE macro


    4 bytes  (nibble index?  9th nibble, so index is 8?)

        32 bits, 28 bits + 4 unused bits, (4 bytes) (I6-I12)

            i6 is data[5]
            i7 is data[5]
            i8 is data[6]
            i9 is data[6]
            i10 is data[7]
            i11 is data[7]
            i12 is data[8]

            zero field is 4 bits    data[8]

    1 byte
        AFRAME is 1 byte        data[9]


